 |f_n (x)| 
 \begin{align*} \sup_{0<x<1} |f_n(x)| &= n^c\cdot \frac{1}{\sqrt{1+2n}} \cdot \left(1-\frac{1}{{1+2n}}\right)^n\\ \lim_{n \rightarrow \infty} \sup_{0<x<1} |f_n(x)| &= \lim_{n \rightarrow \infty} \frac{n^c}{\sqrt{1+2n}} \cdot \left(1-\frac{1}{{1+2n}}\right)^n\\ &=\lim_{n \rightarrow \infty} \frac{n^c}{\sqrt{1+2n}} \cdot \left(\left(1+\frac{-1}{{1+2n}}\right)^{(-1-2n)}\right)^{\frac{n}{-1-2n}}\\ &=\lim_{n \rightarrow \infty} \frac{1}{\sqrt{2}n^{0.5-c}}\cdot e^{-0.5} \end{align*} 
c<0.5 
